metadata.name: Bayerlinge #37
metadata.description:
"Bayerlinge" is motivated by the artworks of Herbert Bayer (1900-1985). The Upper Austrian born artist spent his life in Germany and the United Stated and also worked as graphic designer, painter, and many more.

I was inspired by his piece "Foursome" from 1971 and aimed to deliver the same feeling in a generative setting. The token expands upon Bayer's arrangement, adding different shapes and for more than the overlapping 2x2 setup.

The key press "s" or "S" lets you save a high resolution image.

metadata.name: Loom #97
metadata.description:
Loom is an exploration on texture, points, lines and noise on color in a gridsystem. 

You can self-curate your token, by clicking the canvas colors change in the cells, with the g key you can toggle between local change (cell) or global change (all cells), with the c key you can remove a color, with the v key you can reset colors, with the x key you can download a higher resolution version.


Press 's' to save a png image
Press 'j' to save a jpg image
Press 'x' to save a higher resolution png
Press 'c' to remove a color
Press 'v' to reset colors
